ADVANCED CONCEPTS (IMPORTANT)

ARRAY REFERENCE BEHAVIOR

let arr1 = [1, 2];
let arr2 = arr1;

arr2.push(3);

console.log(arr1); // [1,2,3]

👉 Both point to same array (reference)

COPY ARRAY PROPERLY

let arr1 = [1, 2];
let arr2 = [...arr1];
QUICK SUMMARY
Array stores multiple values
Index starts from 0
Use push/pop for add/remove
slice = copy
splice = modify
Arrays are objects
Use loops to traverse
